label: gametocyte detection assay
definition: An assay that detects parasite gametocyte in a specimen.

label: malaria rapid diagnosis test
definition: An assay that is quick and easy in the diagnosis of malaria by detecting evidence of malaria parasites (antigens) in human blood.

label: organismal body temperature measurement assay
definition: An assay that detects body temperature of an organism.

label: parasite detection assay
definition: An assay that detects parasite in a specimen.

label: feces microbiology assay
definition: Assay that subjects a feces specimen to a test for microorganisms.

label: blood test
definition: A laboratory test that has a blood specimen as specified input.

label: falcivax rapid diagnostic test
definition: A laboratory test that can quickly establishing the diagnosis of  P. falciparum or P. vivax malaria infection by detecting the antigens in a person's blood.

label: optimal-IT rapid diagnostic test
definition: A laboratory test that is a rapid, sensitive malaria test that is able to differentiate between P. falciparum and other malaria parasites.

label: urine test
definition: A laboratory test that has a urine specimen as specified input.

label: parasite species identification by PCR assay
definition: An organism identification assay that identifies the species of parasites by PCR.

label: parasite detection by PCR assay
definition: An assay that detects parasite in a specimen using PCR.

label: feces test
definition: A laboratory test that has a feces specimen as specified input.

label: cerebrospinal fluid test
definition: A laboratory test that has a cerebrospinal fluid specimen as specified input.

label: endotracheal aspirate test
definition: A laboratory test that has a endotracheal aspirate specimen as specified input.

label: saliva test
definition: A laboratory test that has a saliva specimen as specified input.

label: induced sputum test
definition: A laboratory test that has an induced sputum specimen as specified input.

label: cerebrospinal fluid microbiology assay
definition: Assay that subjects a cerebrospinal fluid specimen to a test for microorganisms.

label: endotracheal aspirate microbiology assay
definition: Assay that subjects a endotracheal aspirate specimen to a test for microorganisms.

label: induced sputum microbiology assay
definition: Assay that subjects an induced sputum specimen to a test for microorganisms.

label: pleural fluid microbiology assay
definition: Assay that subjects a pleural fluid specimen to a test for microorganisms.
